### Page builder blocks (`apps/web/src/components/sections/`)

- Each block’s root `<section>` carries CMS background (`style` from `usePageBuilderBlockRoot()`), `data-sanity` for Presentation, and the kebab-case `_type` class only — **do not** put `container-wrapper` or `py-*` padding on that `<section>`.
- Wrap non-nested content in `<div className="container-wrapper …">` (plus block-specific `py-*` as needed). Skip that wrapper when `isNested` is true (blocks inside `twoColumns`, `section`, `cta`, etc.).

### Component Structure

- Prefer `grid` over `flex` unless working with two sibling tags
- Use `flex` for simple parent-child layouts:

```jsx
<div>
  <img />
  <p>Some text</p>
</div>
```

- Always use appropriate semantic HTML
- Use `SanityImage` for any images generated in Sanity if the component is available
- Use `Buttons.tsx` resolver for any buttons unless specified otherwise
- Button style standard: `default` and `outline` variants must use `80px` border radius
- Button color standard: `default`/primary button background must be `#d52c5a` (hover `#cc0047`)

## Internationalization Rules

Only apply these rules when specifically asked about internationalization:

| Replace | With |
|---------|------|
| left | start |
| right | end |
| ml | ms |
| mr | me |
| pl | ps |
| pr | pe |
| border-l | border-s |
| border-r | border-e |
| text-left | text-start |
| text-right | text-end |
| float-left | float-start |
| float-right | float-end |

For buttons with directional arrows, use an RTL prop to correctly handle horizontal inversion.